description.description_en: A perennial, pubescent, erect herb, 40–150 cm high.Radical and cauline leaves long-petiolate, ternate-bipinnate, lateral and terminal leaflets ovate-lanceolate, cordate, truncate or obtuse at base, acuminate at apex, 7–13 cm long, 2–5 cm wide, the margins duplicate-serrate.Inflorescence terminal, paniculate, 30–60 cm long, the axis with short glandular hairs; flowers white, small, short pedicellate; calyx 5-lobed, the lobes ovate, 1.5–2 mm long; petals spathulate, about 1 mm long; stamens 10.Capsules about 4 mm long; seeds small, numerous.
